📌What is Amazon ElastiCache?
                    Amazon ElastiCache is a fully managed in-memory caching service by AWS. 
                    It improves application performance by storing frequently accessed data in memory (RAM) instead of fetching it from a database every time. It supports two engines — Redis and Memcached.

🚀 Part 1 — Create ElastiCache (Redis):
          Step 1 — Navigate:
                  Go to AWS Console → Search "ElastiCache" → Click "ElastiCache"
                  In the left panel → Click "Cache" (or "Redis caches")
                  Click "Create Cache" ✅
          Step 2 — Choose Cache Engine:
                  Setting	Value
                  Engine	Redis ✅
          Step 3 — Deployment Option:
                   Setting	              Value
                  Deployment Option	    Node-based cluster ✅
          Step 4 — Creation Method:
                    Setting	          Value
                    Creation Method	    Cluster Cache ✅
          Step 5 — Cluster Mode:
                    Setting	      Value
                    Cluster Mode	  Disabled ✅ 
          Step 6 — Cluster Settings (Leave Remaining as Default):
                   Setting	        Value
                    Cluster Name	  Leave as default or enter a custom name
                    Engine Version	Leave as default (latest stable)
                    Port	          6379 (default Redis port)
                    Parameter Group	Leave as default
                    Node Type	Leave as default (e.g. cache.t3.micro)
                    💡 All remaining settings in this section can be left as-is for demo purposes.
                    
          Step 7 — Cache Settings (Number of Replicas):
                    Setting	Value
                    Number of Replicas	0 ✅
                    ⚠️ Note: Setting replicas to 0 means no standby/replica nodes 
                    — if the primary node fails, there is no automatic failover. Fine for demo/learning. For Production 
                    — use at least 1 replica for high availability.
          Step 8 — Subnet Group:
                    Setting	          Value
                      Subnet Group	Create new → demo-subnet-groups ✅
                      💡 Subnet groups define which VPC subnets your ElastiCache cluster will be placed in. Always ensure the subnet group matches the VPC your application lives in.
          
          Step 9 — Click Next ✅
====================================================================================================================
🔐 Part 2 — Security Settings:
        Step 1 — Security Configuration:
                Setting	                        Value
                Encryption at Rest	            Disabled (for demo)
                Encryption in Transit (TLS)	    Disabled (for demo)
                Redis AUTH Token	              Disabled (for demo)
                ⚠️ Security Note: Disabling all security settings is only acceptable for demo/learning purposes.
                For Production — always enable:
                
                ✅ Encryption at Rest — protects stored data
                ✅ Encryption in Transit (TLS) — protects data moving between app and cache
                ✅ Redis AUTH Token — requires a password to connect to Redis
        Step 2 — Click Next ✅ and review and create
